function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(x -> isuppercase(x[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` function in Julia, which allows us to filter elements from a collection based on a condition. In this case, the condition is `isuppercase(x[1])`, which checks if the first character of the word `x` is uppercase. If the condition is true, the word is included in the output list. If it is not true, the word is excluded.
